    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You should subclass "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "UIActivity"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " only if you want to provide custom services to the user. A service takes data that is passed to it, does something to that data, and returns the results. For example, a social media service might take whatever text, images, or other content is provided to it and post them to the user’s account. Activity objects are used in conjunction with a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivityviewcontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object, which is responsible for presenting services to the user. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The system already provides support for many standard services and makes them available through the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivityviewcontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object. For example, the standard activity view controller supports emailing data, posting items to one of the user’s social media accounts, and several other options. You do not have to provide custom services for any of the built-in types."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Subclassing Notes",
          "anchor": "1676052"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This class must be subclassed before it can be used. The job of an activity object is to act on the data provided to it and to provide some meta information that iOS can display to the user. For more complex services, an activity object can also display a custom user interface and use it to gather additional information from the user. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 4,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Methods to Override",
          "anchor": "1676054"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When subclassing, you must always override the following methods and use them to provide information about your service:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620671-activitytype"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620674-activitytitle"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620658-activityimage"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620677-canperformwithactivityitems"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620668-preparewithactivityitems"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620656-activitycategory"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If your "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620677-canperformwithactivityitems"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method indicates that your subclass is able to operate on the specified data, the active "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivityviewcontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object displays your service to the user. When the user selects your service, the activity view controller calls the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620668-preparewithactivityitems"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method followed by only one of these methods: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620678-activityviewcontroller"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "—Returns a view controller to present to the user. If your service requires additional input from the user, override this method and use it to return the view controller object responsible for presenting your custom UI. (You do not need to present the view controller yourself.) After your view controller object gathers the needed input, it is responsible for initiating the task associated with the service."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiactivity/1620659-performactivity"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "—Performs the service without displaying any additional UI. If your service does not need additional input from the user, override this method and perform the task associated with the service. "
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
